cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV. 

This paper is about attacks on federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses attacks on the security of the federated learning system, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses optimization techniques to formulate the attacks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses real-world datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the attacks on computer vision models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
